It could also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category as it involves analyzing global urban land-use inventory. Additionally, it could be categorized under Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves training GANs. The paper also involves analyzing spatial organization, which could fall under the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, it could be categorized under Computational Geometry (cs.CY) as it involves analyzing urban spatial metrics.
